data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-394_ pf-heading-2-h3"><font color="#4da32d"><span style="color: rgb(251, 162, 14);">MODERATE</span></font></h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-396_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To understand the urgency of taking action, consider that breathing air containing 2 pCi/L of radon has the same impact on an adult lung as smoking 4&nbsp;cigarettes a day.</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-398_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-399_ pf-heading-2-h3"><font color="#4da32d"><span style="color: rgb(208, 2, 27);">HIGH RISK</span></font></h3><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-401_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">If the average indoor radon level exceeds the action level of 4 pCi/L prescribed by the EPA, it‚Äôs crucial to immediately contact a certified radon professional. </p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-7f90" data-category="FAQs" data-name="Lovey" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fsvrPk eTuePL pf-403_ pf-color-scheme-2"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eNSrbD jPuwGZ"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-404_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-405_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-406_ pf-heading-2-h3">Common Questions</h3></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-408_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-409_"><div class="sc-dcJtft hisXnU pf-410_ pf-icon-right" data-scrolling="false" data-multiple="false" data-pf-type="Accordion"><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-411_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-412_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="f7b216a9-87d2-45b9-a5a8-a34bf432cb99" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Which room in the house should I test for radon?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="f7b216a9-87d2-45b9-a5a8-a34bf432cb99" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-414_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-415_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-416_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-417_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To test for radon, start with the lowest livable area of your home, such as a basement or ground floor, since radon levels are typically highest there. Focus on rooms that are frequently used, avoiding areas with high humidity, heat&nbsp;and ventilation. Choose a centrally located room on the floor being tested to get the most reliable results, and ensure there are no physical barriers that could affect air flow and the accuracy of the reading.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-419_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-420_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="25a8a34b-f432-4b99-b17d-5e1efc8bba9f" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Can I move my radon detector to a different room?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="25a8a34b-f432-4b99-b17d-5e1efc8bba9f" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-422_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-423_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-424_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-425_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Yes, you can move your radon detector to a different room. Monitor radon levels in one area of your house for at least several days before relocating the device to a new spot.<br><br>For the most accurate results, reset the device before moving it to another location, saving the existing data for future comparison.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-427_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-428_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="f17d5e1e-fc8b-4a9f-aff4-9ac6aa9f4aa6" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>I've been told not to enter the room during a radon test. Is this also true for home radon monitors?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="f17d5e1e-fc8b-4a9f-aff4-9ac6aa9f4aa6" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-430_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-431_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-432_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-433_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With Ecosense digital radon detectors, there's no need to avoid entering the room during monitoring. These detectors are designed to sample indoor air for radon while you continue with your regular activities, providing insight into typical radon exposure levels. <br><br>To ensure accurate readings, it's important to minimize sudden changes in ventilation. For instance, avoid leaving windows wide open, especially during short-term tests. The Ecosense detector seamlessly integrates into your daily routine, offering a clear and continuous picture of radon levels based on your occupancy patterns.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-435_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-436_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="6ff49ac6-aa9f-4aa6-a0e6-d997c43f23bf" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>Is short term test enough to determine that I need to call a radon professional?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="6ff49ac6-aa9f-4aa6-a0e6-d997c43f23bf" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-438_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-439_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-440_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-441_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With Ecosense technology, you receive your first reading in just 10 minutes and reliable results within an hour. It achieves over 90% accuracy after 10 hours of monitoring. A short-term radon test can provide an initial indication of radon levels in your home. <br><br>However, it's typically recommended to follow up with a long-term test if the initial short-term test shows elevated radon levels (above 4 pCi/L or 148 Bq/m¬≥). The advantage of a digital radon detector is that you can continuously monitor without needing to switch devices, ensuring ongoing measurement of radon levels in your home.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Accordion.Content.Wrapper" class="sc-iGgVNO dygSQz pf-443_"><button type="button" class="sc-eqUzNf hEUCJf pf-444_ pf-anchor" data-header-id="20e6d997-c43f-43bf-85ac-e702b465a0b1" data-active="false" data-pf-type="Accordion.Header"><i class="pfa pfa-chevron-right pfa-arrow"></i><span>For how long should I wait before calling a radon professional?</span></button><div data-pf-expandable="true" data-id="20e6d997-c43f-43bf-85ac-e702b465a0b1" style="display:none" data-pf-type="Accordion.Content" class="sc-fqkwJk gxNUkH pf-446_"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-447_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-448_"><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-449_ pf-text-2" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With Ecosense technology, you achieve over 90% accuracy after 10 hours of monitoring. If you're uncertain about the results, consider short-term monitoring, which typically lasts 2-7 days. If the short-term results confirm high radon levels, it's crucial to contact a radon professional promptly. <br><br>For results showing low levels or significant fluctuations, consider a long-term monitoring for minimum of 3 months to a year or longer for a thorough assessment. Upon confirming elevated radon levels above the recommended thresholds (usually 4 pCi/L or 148 Bq/m¬≥), it's advisable to consult with a qualified radon mitigation professional to explore options for reducing radon levels in your home.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-1c4e" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-fsvrPk eTuePL pf-451_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eNSrbD jPuwGZ"><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-452_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-453_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cVzzKN eMDdXJ pf-454_ pf-heading-1-h3"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bOQUxc quwHz pf-456_">Still have a question?</span></h3><p class="sc-bJBfJu eVDjFe pf-457_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bOQUxc quwHz pf-459_">Please email us at <u><span style="color: rgb(50, 169, 218);"><span style="color: rgb(50, 169, 218);"><span style="color: rgb(61, 181, 230);">support@ecosense.io</span></span></span></u> or fill out the support form below.<br>Tell us about the challenge you‚Äôre experiencing and we‚Äôll get back to you within 24 hours.</span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-